bioghist.p:
Edmund John Catrow was a marine who served in the following units during World War II:
        Second Joint Assault Signal Company, Field Signal Battalion; First Battalion, Sixth Marines;
        H & S Company, Sixth Marines; First Battalion, Eighth Marines; Regimental Weapons
        Military Police Company, Eighth Marines; Division Signal Company, Second Marine Division;
        and First Battalion, Twenty-Eighth Marines, Fifth Marine Division.
